%\subsection{Closed Huygens\rq~Box}\label{Closed_Huygen_s_Box} \index{Huygens\rq~Box}

{\LARGE T}o calculate the far-zone-field pattern, FDTD technique with six-sided rectangular box of virtual surface locus S that encloses the structure of interest in the scattering field-zone of FDTD lattice, known as Huygens\rq~Box\index{FDTD!Huygens\rq~Box}\index{Huygens\rq~Box} is considered. The electric and magnetic current on the closed Huygens\rq~surface are computed by using the FDTD technique, and the far-field pattern is subsequently obtained from the equivalent current sources as shown in the Fig.~\ref{Fig:near_to_far_field_trans}. As the electric and magnetic fields have a half-cell of deviation in Yee\rq s scheme; the fields on the Huygens\rq~surface are averaged from those around the surface, shown in Fig.~\ref{Fig:equivalent_field_on_the_surface_of_Huygen_box}.





